sponsor: Fujifilm Kyowa Kirin Biologics Co., Ltd.
briefTitle: A Study to Compare FKB327 Long-term Safety, Efficacy and Immunogenicity With Humira® in Rheumatoid Arthritis Patients
officialTitle: An Open-label Extension Study to Compare the Long-term Efficacy, Safety, Immunogenicity and Pharmacokinetics of FKB327 and Humira® in Patients With Rheumatoid Arthritis on Concomitant Methotrexate
summary: The purpose of the study is to compare the long-term safety, effectiveness and immunogenicity of FKB327 in comparison to Humira® in rheumatoid arthritis patients who have completed study FKB327-002 and have inadequate disease control on methotrexate.

primaryOutcome.measure: Number of Patients With Adverse Events as a Measure of Safety Per Treatment Group in Period I
primaryOutcome.timeFrame: Period I: from Week 0 up until Week 30;
